      en: {
        metaTitle: "Taxi Marseille → Cannes | Fixed price from €240 | TaxiNeo",
        metaDescription: "Taxi Marseille → Cannes. 175 km, 2h, fixed price from €240. Festival, Croisette, congress. Book 24/7.",
        heroTitle: "Taxi Marseille → Cannes",
        heroSubtitle: "Your Marseille → Cannes transfer at €240 — €300. 175 km via the A8.",
        description: "Cannes, city of the Film Festival and international congresses, is 2h from Marseille via the A8 through the Esterel.",
        routeDescription: "The route takes the A8 via Aix-en-Provence, Brignoles and the Esterel massif. Exit Cannes / Mougins.",
        introduction: "Cannes is synonymous with glamour, cinema and major international events. The Cannes Film Festival in May transforms the Croisette into the world's red carpet, MIPIM in March brings together global real estate, MIPCOM in October gathers the audiovisual industry, and the Cannes Lions festival attracts creatives from around the globe. But Cannes is much more than a festival city: it is also a prestigious seaside resort with fine sandy beaches, its old port overlooked by Le Suquet (the old town), and the Lérins Islands accessible by boat (Sainte-Marguerite Island with the Man in the Iron Mask fort, Saint-Honorat Island with its wine-producing monastery). The Palais des Festivals, the Carlton, the Martinez and the Majestic are legendary Riviera addresses. From Marseille, taxis are particularly popular during congress periods as Cannes hotels are mobbed and many delegates stay in Marseille or Aix-en-Provence. A taxi is also ideal for transfers from Marseille Provence Airport when direct flights to Nice are fully booked or too expensive.",
        itineraire: "Your driver leaves Marseille via the A7 towards Aix-en-Provence, then joins the A8 towards Nice at the Trois Pigeons interchange. The motorway crosses the Provençal plateau between vineyards and garrigue, passes Saint-Maximin-la-Sainte-Baume and Brignoles, then Le Luc en Provence. After Le Muy, you enter the Esterel massif: red porphyry rocks sculpted by erosion create a lunar and grandiose landscape. The motorway overlooks the sea with spectacular views between Fréjus and Théoule-sur-Mer. The Cannes-Mougins exit (exit 42) leads to the expressway towards central Cannes, the Palais des Festivals and the Croisette. Tolls amount to approximately €18. Under normal conditions, the journey takes 2 hours. During the Cannes Film Festival (two weeks in May), the approaches to the city are very congested — allow 15-20 extra minutes for the last kilometre to the Croisette.",
        conseils: "If heading to Cannes for a congress (MIPIM, MIPCOM, Cannes Lions, Film Festival), book your taxi at least 48h in advance: demand is extremely high during these events. For the Film Festival in May, only accredited guests can access the Palais des Festivals — ask your driver to drop you on Boulevard de la Croisette or at the Palais car park. Returns after the red carpet (around 10-11pm) require advance booking as taxis are swamped. For beaches, the public Croisette beaches are free and alternate with private hotel beaches (expect €30-50 per sun lounger). For luxury shopping, Rue d'Antibes is brand paradise, running parallel to the Croisette. If time permits, a trip to the Lérins Islands (boat from the old port, 15 min) is absolutely worthwhile — the Man in the Iron Mask fort is fascinating.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Marseille — Cannes costs €25-30 and takes 2h to 2h30 with a change at Toulon or Les Arcs. There is no direct TGV. The Zou! LR35 bus offers tickets at €20 for 2h30. By car, expect €22 in fuel and €18 in tolls, totalling €40 excluding parking (Cannes city centre parking costs €20-35/day). The TaxiNeo taxi at €240 — €300 provides premium door-to-door service stress-free — essential during major Cannes events when even car parks are full. For 3 passengers with congress luggage, the taxi works out to €80-100 per person, a reasonable business expense.",
        faq: [
          { question: "Can the taxi drop me directly at the Palais des Festivals?", answer: "Yes, your driver drops you as close as possible to the Palais des Festivals. During the Film Festival, traffic restrictions apply but we know the authorised drop-off zones." },
          { question: "How long is the journey during the Cannes Film Festival?", answer: "Allow 2h15 to 2h30 during the Film Festival in May. Cannes approaches are heavily congested, especially in the evening during screenings. Plan an extra 30 min margin." },
          { question: "Can I stop in Aix-en-Provence on the way?", answer: "Yes, a stop in Aix-en-Provence (Cours Mirabeau, old Aix) is possible for a €25 supplement and 20-30 min detour. The A8 passes just north of Aix." },
          { question: "Does the taxi serve Croisette hotels?", answer: "Yes, we serve all hotels: Carlton, Martinez, Majestic, Grand Hyatt, JW Marriott and all others. Your driver drops you at the entrance." },
          { question: "Is a return taxi Cannes → Marseille available in the evening?", answer: "Yes, we provide Cannes → Marseille returns 24/7, including after Festival screenings (10pm-midnight). Book ahead to guarantee availability." }
        ],
      },
