        routeDescription: "50 km — approximately 40 minutes via A50",
        introduction: "Bandol is one of the most elegant seaside resorts on the Var coast, world-famous for its AOC Bandol appellation, one of Provence's most prestigious red wines. Its colourful marina, golden sandy beaches (Renécros beach, Central beach) and secret coves make it a popular destination year-round. The journey from Marseille takes the A50 motorway along the Provençal coastline, offering glimpses of the calanques and Toulon harbour in the distance. Bandol is also the departure point for Bendor Island, a small paradise created by Paul Ricard, accessible in 7 minutes by shuttle.",
        itineraire: "From Marseille, take the A50 towards Toulon. The motorway passes through the Joliette tunnel then runs along Marseille's southern districts. After Aubagne and La Ciotat, take exit 11 'Bandol / Sanary'. The descent to Bandol takes 5 minutes via the D559. The route is simple and direct. Alternatively, the coastal road (D559) via Cassis and La Ciotat offers sublime scenery along the calanques but adds 30 minutes. Wine lovers can request a detour via the Bandol wine route, between Le Castellet and La Cadière-d'Azur.",
